# Week 13 - Day 6: Largest BST in Binary Tree

## 📌 Problem Statement
Given a Binary Tree, find the size of the largest subtree that is also a Binary Search Tree (BST).

---

## 🚀 Approach

We use a **bottom-up (postorder traversal)** approach.

For every node, we check:
- Left subtree info
- Right subtree info

We create a helper class `Info` that stores:
- `min` → Minimum value in subtree
- `max` → Maximum value in subtree
- `sz` → Size of largest BST

---

## 🧠 Key Logic

A subtree is a BST if:
  
If valid:
- Size = left.sz + right.sz + 1

If not valid:
- Return max size of left or right subtree

---

## ⚡ Time Complexity
- **O(N)** → Each node is visited once

## 💾 Space Complexity
- **O(H)** → Recursive stack (height of tree)

---

## 🧾 Code
  #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Node
{
public:
    int data;
    Node *left;
    Node *right;

    Node(int val)
    {
        data = val;
        left = right = NULL;
    }
};

Node *insert(Node *root, int val)
{
    if (root == NULL)
    {
        return new Node(val);
    }

    if (val < root->data)
    {
        root->left = insert(root->left, val);
    }
    else
    {
        root->right = insert(root->right, val);
    }
    return root;
}

// creation of binary search tree
Node *buildBST(vector<int> arr)
{
    Node *root = NULL;
    for (int val : arr)
    {
        root = insert(root, val);
    }
    return root;
}

// find size of largest BST in BT
class Info
{
public:
    int min, max, sz;

    Info(int mi,int mx,int size){
        min = mi;
        max = mx;
        sz = size;
    }
};

Info helper(Node* root){
    if(root==NULL){
        return Info(INT_MAX,INT_MIN,0);
    }

    Info left = helper(root->left);
    Info right = helper(root->right);

    if(root->data > left.max && root->data < right.min){
       int currMin = min(root->data,left.min);
       int currMax = max(root->data,right.max);
       int currsz = left.sz + right.sz + 1;

       return Info(currMin,currMax,currsz);
    }

    // else case in this case the valied bst is not exist
    return Info(INT_MIN,INT_MAX,max(left.sz,right.sz));
}


int largestBSTinBT(Node* root){
Info info = helper(root);
return info.sz; // size of max bstinbt
}


int main()
{
    vector<int> arr = {3, 2, 1, 5, 6, 4};
    Node *root = buildBST(arr);
    cout<<largestBSTinBT(root)<<" ";
    return 0;
}
